To be completely honest, not my favourite flavour combination. I was pretty stingy on the chocolate and used dark chocolate so perhaps other loaves had more sugar and spices to even out the sour taste. The warm, cozy pumpkin spice flavours with the lactic tang of sourdough and earthy notes of the chocolate just wasn't the best. Don't get me wrong, it was still delicious. Especially toasted with some cream cheese when it gets slightly soft and melted - so good. But sweet breads are just simply better with yeast moving forward. 

