Date: 2025-12-24 to 2025-12-25

Technically my first sourdough bake was my sourdough bagels which turned out pretttyyyy bad. It was completely underproofed and sank to the bottom when boiling... ended up tasting half decent after baking but was totally dense and tough. Not my best work and I will try again some day...

My first real bake would be a sourdough jalapeno cheddar loaf ([Recipe](https://www.feastingathome.com/jalapeno-cheddar-cheese-bread/) by Feasting At Home). I did a counter-only bulk ferment and proof and added in the cheddar inclusions during the shaping right before baking. 

