Overall, pretty proud of my first sourdough bake. It was cheesy with a nice sourdough tang, nothing too strong or acidic. The texture was a little gummier than expected but that's to be expected for my first attempt. I was pleased to see that the toppings of poppy seeds and sesame didn't burn and stuck on nicely to the loaf (a quick misting of water worked well). In hindsight, a smaller loaf would've been better, since I have a smaller loaf pan. I forgot how much flour/water I used but it looks like the full loaf or 90% at the very least. Adding the inclusions at the end during shaping also likely flattened out some of the air bubbles. I remember that trying to transfer the fully puffed bread roll to the tin was terrible and resembled more of a fish flop than a smooth transfer. The bread also could've been baked longer, seeing the lightly browned crust and the gummy interior. I also didn't score the bread, so it cracked horizontally rather than a controlled seam along the length. Was still delicious toasted or by itself so pretty pleased with this one. 


